Description: Body sherd of East Greek black-figured pottery dinos or krater; interior glazed, fired red; exterior: on left, foreleg of deer or goat to right; part of a long-legged, hairy feline to right, its body and legs covered with short incised strokes; preserved: hind legs, part of hindquarters, belly (red stripe) and foreleg (?; red stripe); below picture, single line and part of lower frieze.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B102.25)
CVA British Museum 8 / Corpus Vasorum Antiquorum: Great Britain 13, British Museum 8 (pl. 8, no. 12)
